Description: Unified manager for installed applications
 Terminator is a GTK4/libadwaita application that lists installed apps from
 multiple Linux packaging systems — system packages (via PackageKit),
 Flatpak, Snap, AppImage, and user-local desktop entries — in a single
 interface, and lets you uninstall any of them.
